# Excalidraw Changelog Standards

## Change Types

Group entries under one of these sections:

- **Features** — new features
- **Fixes** — bug fixes
- **Chore** — non-src changes (e.g. `package.json`, config)
- **Refactor** — refactoring with no behavior change
- **Breaking changes** — API or behavior changes requiring migration

## Structure

```markdown
## Unreleased

### Features

- Short description of what was added. [#123](https://github.com/excalidraw/excalidraw/pull/123)

### Fixes

- Short description of what was fixed. [#456](https://github.com/excalidraw/excalidraw/pull/456)
```

- `## Unreleased` at the top — no brackets
- Add new entries at the top of the correct section
- PR link at the end of the entry, no enclosing parentheses: `[#123](url)`
- Entries may include code blocks for API examples

## Entry Quality

Good — specific, user-facing, with PR link:
`- Fixed race condition in element rendering. [#128](https://github.com/excalidraw/excalidraw/pull/128)`

Bad — vague, no link:
`- Fixed bug`

## Rules

- Update with every PR
- Place the latest change at the top of the correct section
- Include PR link for every entry
- Skip internal-only changes with no user impact

## How to verify

1. Confirm `## Unreleased` (no brackets) exists at the top of `CHANGELOG.md`
2. Verify section headers use `### Features`, `### Fixes`, `### Chore`, `### Refactor`, or `### Breaking changes`
3. Verify every new entry has a PR link in the format `[#123](url)` (no enclosing parentheses)
4. Confirm the new entry is placed at the top of its section

## A/B TEST RESULTS
─────────────────────────────
Target: .cursor/rules/changelog.mdc   Type: Rule
Prompt: "Write a changelog entry for a new feature that adds support for locking elements so they can't be moved or edited."
─────────────────────────────

── A (ENABLED) ──
```markdown
## Unreleased

### Features

- Added element locking: locked shapes and other elements stay fixed on the
  canvas and can't be moved, resized, rotated, or edited until unlocked
  (from the context menu or properties). [#123](https://github.com/excalidraw/excalidraw/pull/123)
```

Formatting choices: under ### Features (user-visible capability), one user-facing sentence, link format #123 with no enclosing parens.

── B (DISABLED) ──
```markdown
## Excalidraw Library

### Features

- Added support for locking elements so they cannot be moved or edited.
  [#XXXX](https://github.com/excalidraw/excalidraw/pull/XXXX)
```

Formatting choices: derived from file structure; placed under

Excalidraw Library → ### Features; bullet and PR link style match
existing entries.

### Comparison

| Aspect              | A (Enabled)                                   | B (Disabled)                                                    |
|---------------------|-----------------------------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------|
| Followed rule?      | Yes                                           | N/A — derived from file                                         |
| Top-level heading   | `## Unreleased` (rule-specified)              | `## Excalidraw Library` (inferred)                              |
| Section header      | `### Features` ✓                              | `### Features` ✓                                                |
| PR link format      | `[#123](url)` — no parens ✓                   | `[#XXXX](url)` — no parens ✓                                    |
| Entry wording       | User-facing, descriptive                      | Minimal but correct                                             |
| Structural accuracy | Correct (new entries go at top of Unreleased) | Invented `## Excalidraw Library` heading not in the actual file |
